  "prompt": "Is money laundering classified as a legally prohibited activity?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in most jurisdictions around the world, including China. It involves the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses, to make the funds appear as if they originate from legitimate sources.\n\nIn China, the Anti-Money Laundering Law and other related regulations explicitly prohibit money laundering activities. The Chinese government has established stringent measures and a comprehensive legal framework to combat such illegal financial activities, including strengthening the monitoring of financial transactions and cooperating with international efforts to clamp down on money laundering. The Chinese law enforcement agencies are actively combating money laundering to maintain financial order and national security.",
